Preface

This document will serve as a thorough guide for how to build and play Deadeye for the current live Western version. It is designed to be a living document, which means it is dynamically changing based on new information from both the Western and KR playerbases. The goal of this document is to help both beginners and experienced players get a deeper understanding of their class by answering questions and by providing them with comprehensive information and details that are otherwise not apparent or made obvious by the game.

General FAQ

Questions are sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord #Deadeye

This section is ever-growing, and new FAQ submissions are always welcome.

Where can I talk to other Deadeye?

Most of us hang around the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord in the #Deadeye channel.

Feel free to stop by and ask any questions you may have outside this document or to give us any suggestions on improvements to the guide.

(Requires Deadeye role).

Why play Deadeye?

Deadeye is an incredibly flashy and mobile class (particularly true with swiftness) that brings an extremely valuable class synergy. Deadeye is able to perform well in all types of content and can be a very satisfying character to play. You can opt for the Enhanced Weapon build—which provides a high APM weapon-swapping play style focused on doing incredible bursts of damage—or its dual handgun-wielding counterpart, Pistoleer—which offers some of the most consistent DPS in the game to steadily whittle down your opponents.

What is the identity gimmick for Deadeye?

Deadeyes, like Gunslingers, are characterized by their signature weapon wheel, where each stance has a defining trait that changes the playstyle and the skills available.
Handgun skills provide utility, mobility and mid range damage,  Shotgun focuses on slow and close damage, while Rifle skills are long range damage.

IMPORTANT: The grayed out squares will indicate that the corresponding skills on the keyboard are on cooldown or not available (shotgun only has skills on QWER, while rifle only has skills on ASDF). Meanwhile, colored ones represent an ability that is available for use.

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

For further information, read the respective sections of this document.

Enhanced Weapon

Pistoleer

Summary

Enhanced Weapon provides Critical Chance bonus on every weapon swap.
Their builds use either all three or only weapons of your preference.

Pistoleer is restricted only to the Handgun weapon stance and gets various buffs for it.
It is generally considered easier to play.

Pros

  • Very strong burst
  • Requires no setup or gauge generation.
  • High Mobility
  • A variety of skill builds
  • Has skills for Close, Medium and Long range.
  • Has many weak point skills
  • High consistent DPS
  • High mobility
  • Inexpensive Build
  • Non-positional*
    (optional back-attacks)
  • Low cooldowns
  • Few animation locks.
  • Good stagger

Cons

  • Expensive & high investment
  • Meta builds focus on close range & back attack skills
  • Medium-Long animation locks
  • Some mana issues

What are the Pros and Cons of being a Deadeye?

Pros

Cons

General

High Mobility.

These abilities provide more mobility to Deadeye: Somersault Shot, Enforce Execution, Dexterous Shot and Desperado, and his spacebar (evasion ability). With this, Deadeye is able to have a more fluid and more greedy playstyle.

Pistoleer takes this to the extreme by gaining an additional spacebar as well as a buff reducing the cooldown of his evasion ability.

If Not Properly Built, May Be Gated.

People may not know much about Deadeye due to his low popularity so be aware that if you are not properly geared or overly geared, you may not be let into parties.

No Setup for Damage

Deadeyes lack meter gain or orb generation, and no setup is required (besides general gameplay factors). No conditions are attached to an Enhanced Weapon player’s explosive burst or a Pistoleer player’s steady damage.

Squishy

Deadeyes are not the most resilient of classes. When they do get hit, they can’t take a lot of them while on item level/progging. This is as opposed to some other classes.

What are my Party Synergies?

 A synergy is a buff/debuff provided by a player that increases the entire party’s potential in combat. This is pretty essential in PvE activities for Lost Ark and should always be taken in consideration when planning team compositions for high-end content. 

Weakness Exposure

Consistent 10% Crit Rate Increase

Skill

 Spiral Tracker (6 seconds)

 AT02 Grenade (8 seconds)

 Equilibrium* (12 seconds)

Please note that these synergies are only applied to you and your party. People in the other party do not benefit, even if the debuffs are applied to the boss.

Is Deadeye a good alt?

 

Enhanced Weapon alt squeezing your pockets

While Enhanced Weapon is very expensive and requires a large amount of investment, Pistoleer is one of the most affordable playstyles to build.

Effectiveness

Enhanced Weapon has high damage as an entropy class. There is a lot of mobility to assist with positioning, but it can be challenging.  Pistoleer is simple to play and effective enough for most content.

 Enhanced Weapon

  • Extremely high damage ceiling

 Pistoleer

  • Simple to play since locked only to pistol stance, non-positional, and has a lower ceiling to hit
  • Decent stagger
  • High damage floor and ceiling

Does Deadeye have good stagger?

Deadeyes have exceptionally good stagger for a DPS class, mainly on their shotgun and rifle abilities. Their most notable stagger skill is Last Request, a shotgun skill that is often paired with the Legendary Overwhelm rune to increase its effectiveness (see next section to maximize this stagger).  

Pistoleers benefit from an innate 40% stagger increase on their skills,

What are Modifiers?

Modifiers are a bonus to skills with the Front/Back Attack affix when used correctly.

Back Attack: +10% Crit Rate, +5% Damage

Front Attack: +10% Stagger, +20% Damage

Enhanced Weapon

Shotgun skills benefit from the Back Attack affix, which grants them a bonus and increased damage from Entropy and Ambush Master.  Last Request has both affixes, which means you can use it as a Front Attack for more stagger or when you can’t Back Attack reliably.

Pistoleer

Pistoleer has four main damage skills with the Back Attack affix.
It is recommended to back-attack if you can, but not mandatory. To avoid having skills off cooldown, it is advised to cast them even when regardless of your current position.

Does Deadeye have good weak point?

Deadeyes also have a decent amount of weak point skills, but it takes a while to cycle through them as they are spread out across all three weapons. Their most notable ability for WP is Cruel Tracker, a pistol skill which has two mutually exclusive tripods for destruction:  Enforce Execution, which applies Level 1 WP on its first stage: Quick Draw, which applies Level 1 WP twice, and Explosive Bullet, which applies level 2 weak point once.

When does a Deadeye begin to feel good to play?

Although Enhanced Weapon Deadeye’s playstyle does not change significantly from when you first start playing him, he will feel relatively weak in comparison to other classes at the same level. This is due to initial low damage numbers which are eventually bolstered with the full Entropy Set, 4x3 engravings (at least), and the correct stats. For this particular build, it will take a significant amount of time, commitment, and gold investment to be a rewarding experience.

What are the key habits of a good Deadeye player?

Both Playstyles

  • Having your Crit buff/Crit Resistance debuff on the boss at all times.
  • Maintaining Adrenaline stacks.
  • High uptime of skills on boss.

Enhanced Weapon

  • Making sure you have your Enhanced Weapon buff up at all times, especially before using your Awakening and main damage skills (you may have to switch to another weapon and back if you want to continue using the same stance).
  • Making sure your shotgun skills are high priority in a rotation.
  • High back attack uptime.
  • Close proximity to the boss for your “Close Shot” tripod to apply (on 3 of 4 shotgun skills).
  • Shotgun stance auto attacks as filler (optional)

Pistoleer

  • Making sure the Conviction and Judgement runes are continuously triggered together when possible.
  • Maintaining spacebar buff
  • Using every skill as soon as it’s available.

What are the key pieces of a Deadeye build?

 Enhanced Weapon

Stats

High Specialization (which directly boosts shotgun damage scaling and pistol Crit Damage), and some Crit or Swiftness.

Engravings

Should prioritize at least Enhanced Weapon 1 for Crit buff and Ambush Master for back attack damage. Apart from that, Enhanced Weapon uses standard damage engravings (Grudge, CD, KBW, Adrenaline).

Tripods

All damage tripods are greatly needed.

Relic Set

The 6 Piece Entropy Set is greatly needed because of reliance on back attack modifiers and Crit.

Pistoleer

Stats

High Specialization (which increases Crit Damage) and high Crit Rate are needed. However, Crit Rate will not necessarily be obtained from accessories (sources from Precise Dagger, Adrenaline, AT02 Grenade, party synergies, etc.).

Engravings

Pistoleer 3 is required for damage with Precise Dagger and Adrenaline for Crit Rate.

Tripods

Some tripods have priority but are not mandatory. Not greatly dependent on them for damage.

Relic Set

The Hallucination or Salvation sets are greatly preferred but not essential.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Enhanced Weapon

Written by qilinggs, Rich, and Jace

Playstyle

Enhanced Weapon Deadeye has a high APM, high-risk, high-reward playstyle where the player’s skill and performance directly translates to damage done. Although this build is extremely rigid in terms of what skills and tripods you should take, the rotation is very flexible with a moveset that offers a decent amount of stagger and weak point.

Gear Set

The Relic Set we use is Earth’s Entropy

Earth’s Entropy is used because we are reliant on Crit and Back Attacks for all of our damage, and the bonuses it provides complements our entire kit.

Nightmare (REQUIRES TESTING) is used for the off-meta Non-positional build.

Like Gunslinger, the Boundless MP effect is extremely undesirable.

 In order to maintain Magick Addiction, Support Mana Buffs and Mana Food may be required. However, if you wish to play this build, here is the guide: Here

Engravings

Here are the Engravings you should aim to use,
and why you would choose specific combinations of Engravings to make a build.

MANDATORY

Enhanced Weapon
Lv.1/3

Crit Rate is increased by 20/25/30% for 9 seconds when you swap weapons.

  • A very efficient engraving to keep at Level 1 as the Crit Rate gained with each Level has minimal increases in power compared to the other engravings you’ll take.
  • Basically has permanent uptime since there is no cooldown for switching between weapons or how often you can refresh this buff. Always try to keep it active.

Adrenaline

Lv.1/2/3

Provides 0.3/0.6/1% Attack Power per stack, and stacks up to 6 times.

At max stacks, it will also give 5/10/15% Crit Rate.

  • Extremely easy to build up and keep max stacks as Deadeye.
  • Synergizes well with Keen Blunt Weapon to offset its drawback.
  • Adren Lv.2/3 + EW Lv.1
  • Adren Lv.1/2 + EW Lv.3

Grudge

Increases damage by 4/10/20% to Boss or above enemies, but you receive 20% more damage from them.

  • An unconditional damage boost against Boss enemies that every DPS should have in their build.
  • Highly recommended to only use at Level 3 due to drawback.

Keen Blunt Weapon

Provides 10/25/50% Crit Damage, but each hit has a 10% chance to deal 20% less damage.

  • Recommended to have at least 75%+ Crit Rate when taking this to make up for the potential losses in damage. This is additive with Entropy.
  • Too much Crit Damage usually suffers from diminishing value, but Deadeye doesn’t have any other better engraving options.

Positional Specific

Ambush Master

Damage is increased by 5/12/25% for back attacks.

  • All shotgun skills benefit from this engraving.
  • This engraving is mandatory if you want to play a positional playstyle

All Out Attack

Increases speed of holding and casting skills by 5/10/20% and 4/10/20% damage to holding and casting skills,

  • Unsure if this is worth taking over other engravings as it only affects certain skills, optional
  • Testing in progress

Other Options

Cursed Doll

Provides 3/8/16% Attack Power, but healing is reduced by 25% from all sources.

  • Unconditional increase in Attack Power at the cost of heals becoming less effective.
  • Recommended to use only at Level 2+ (ideally at Level 3).

Mass Increase

Provides +4/10/18% Attack Power, but Attack Speed is decreased by 10%.

  • Can be used instead of Cursed Doll to avoid the healing penalty.
  • Usable, but not ideal because Deadeye’s shotgun skills are already slow and animation locked (which are only cancelable with space bar).

Ether Predator
Lv.1

Attacking a foe creates an Ether that only you can collect. On collecting the Ether, ATk.Power + 0.2% for 90s and All Defense + 0.3%. Stacks up to 30 times. Chance on Ether collection to increase the stack by 3. (Cooldown:10s).

  • One of the best level 1 options if you are using the others.

5x3+2*

Notes

4x3+2+1

  • Damage difference between the 5x3 Enhanced Weapon 3 build and 4x3+2+1 build is ~3%.
  • Having Enhanced Weapon at only Level 1 and Adrenaline at Level 2 will lower your Crit Rate significantly (15% less Crit Rate than if both were at Level 3), so a Spec/Crit necklace is preferred over Spec/Swift.

5x3 EW3

  • When using a Spec/Crit Necklace, Adrenaline 3 will cause you to overcap on Crit Rate alongside other external buffs (such as party synergies), so Cursed Doll is taken instead for more Attack Power.
  • When with a Spec/Swift Necklace, Adrenaline 3 is taken to make up for the loss in Crit Rate from not having Crit from accessories.

5x3+1

  • Damage difference between the 5x3+Lv.1 EW build and 5x3+Lv.1 Adren build is ~3.56%.

*Since class engraving can’t be at level 1 with full 6/3 Ancient accessories and a 9/7 or 6/10 stone, Adrenaline would be kept at level 1/2 instead of Enhanced Weapon.

AWAKENING

Bursting Flare

Has longer range, higher stagger and was buffed by 20% damage.

Requires all 3 shots to hit for the full stagger and damage, but it is a slow attack and enemies can easily move out of its way during its animations.

Stronger awakening if you can land all hits.

Clay Bombardment

Requires you to be in melee range, but is faster and easier to land. The attack starts from behind you, so you can place your cursor facing away from your target to make it hit earlier than if you were to aim directly at the enemy.

Faster animation. Lower Damage.

Rotations

Damage

or

DISCLAIMER: Enhanced Weapon Deadeye does not have a fixed rotation, but rather skills that should be prioritized and used according to boss patterns.

Burst on Staggered Enemy

Prioritize these 3 skills on staggered enemies. If all cooldowns are up, you will most likely NOT be able to add Shotgun Dominator.

Stagger


If stagger mech is longer than Last Request’s CD (≈23-20 seconds)

  • Use it at the start of the stagger to have it up again for burst.
  • If not, save Last Request for increased damage on stagger.

Destruction

Cruel Tracker will either have two hits of Lv.1 weak point (Quick Draw) or one hit of Lv. 2 weak point (Explosive Bullet). Shotguns are usually not used for checks.

Note: In shorter damage windows, skill priorities generally are: Judgment Day, Shotgun Rapid Fire and Shotgun Dominator, and finally Last Request.
If the enemy is staggered, prioritize Last Request first when taking  Massive Explosion.

Build Notes

If you are a new player and are lacking skill points, run 6M and invest in 4 shotgun and 2 filler skills.

If you do not need additional utility tripods like  Dextrous Shot’s  Excellent Mobility tripod, you may over level your filler skills from 10 to 11/12 to deal more damage.

Purify and Quick Recharge runes can be used on other skills based on preference. If Stagger is not required you can remove Overwhelm from  Last Request

If you’re struggling to pick which fillers to use, click here to review their use cases.

FAQ: Enhanced Weapon

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord #deadeye
This section is ever-growing, and new FAQ submissions are always welcome.

Why play Non-Positional EW?

Non-positional Nightmare EW no longer cares about back attack and plays similar to gunslinger.

It’s damage potential is lower than entropy (≈ 6-10%?), but is easier to achieve.

It is essentially a non-positional class with an emphasis on holding skills, but you still have to use your shotgun skills from close range.

Which fillers are the strongest?

Personal Opinion: All the fillers have contributed roughly about the same damage % depending on skill point investment (lv.10/11/12). Desperado and Aimed shot are very easy to use and are more likely to perform better.  If you go 7m, the last filler can be whatever you like/need.

Spec/Crit or Spec/Swift neck (Entropy)?

The assumption is that since sniper fillers lack 10% crit from back attack, you’re more likely to go for Spec/Crit and Spec/swift if using pistol fillers. Spec/Crit plays slower but high crit rate makes damage consistently high. Spec/Swift may require you to greed more casts using the attack speed in an attempt to get more casts throughout a fight. Ultimately pick what works for you.

What does 6M and 7M mean?

6M and 7M can be interpreted as either Maxed or Main skills. It designates how many damage abilities you will be investing in.

What is “ability queuing?”

For Enhanced Weapon players, ability queuing allows Deadeye or any weapon swapping class to cast an ability on the first frame of swapping to a different weapon. This is valuable because it allows smoother gameplay between switching weapons and more importantly quicker rotations (more DMG) during burst windows. Although, in actual raid gameplay you may not always find yourself using it. In PVP, this could be especially useful as well. Averse goes into more detail about ability queuing here:

Ability Queuing

Conviction/Judgment?

Not recommended. This is because you would have to change your rotations around these Runes since they only reduce cooldowns of skills used 6 seconds after Judgment is activated. Additionally, Enhanced Weapon Deadeyes are not as Mana reliant as Pistoleer Deadeyes. Alternatively, you can use the Quick Recharge Rune for cooldown reduction, which is not as intrusive.

All questions/builds pertaining to Crit Rate and Crit synergies

Deadeyes tend to have plenty of Crit sources so we generally want to make use of them. Ideally, you want to have 85% Crit Rate normally (Keen Blunt Weapon efficiency) and around 100% Crit Rate with party synergies. Some popular/ideal comps are with Gunlancer/Deathblade or Bard/Sorceress, where no other Crit Synergy is available.

Ultimately, build variations are up to player preference. A popular and cheaper build is the BiS 4x3+1 with a Swift/Spec Necklace and Crit/Spec bracelet, which offers lower Crit than recommended, but is still usable in most content.

Can I use Swiftness?

Building Swiftness is up to preference. If the comfort provided by it is a deal breaker, you can run Swiftness at the cost of Crit Rate. However, at the moment, it is only recommended for the Enhanced Weapon 3 build variant with Adrenaline 3. In this build, Swiftness is more viable given the increased Crit Rate from both engravings.

On the other hand, without Swiftness, Spec/Crit builds are dependent on Attack/Move Speed from sources such as Yearning. That being said, these types of builds excel with the right synergies.

Update: Due to not having back attack modifiers, Aimed Shot and One Shot One Kill lack 10% crit rate compared to Quick shot and Cruel Tracker. When using these sniper skills, Spec/Crit necklaces may be preferred.

Swiftness on ring/earring?

Not recommended because you would lose out on Specialization, which is incredibly valuable. If on an alt, technically should be fine as long as you have enough Crit.

Changes to Last Request after the Art of War Patch

With the class changes made back in March, it would be preferable to use Last Request after staggers with the  Massive Explosion tripod. However, since Deadeye’s other skills are lower in stagger value, it’s still recommended to use Last Request with an Overwhelm rune for difficult stagger checks. For staggers caused by countering, start off with Last Request.

Playstyle

Pistoleer is a heavily mobility-focused gunslinging character. With his many movement abilities, the Pistoleer is able to position almost everywhere in a short time and attack his foes from any direction.
While his lacking armor and defense make him a soft target, he is always able to dodge their attacks.

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

  • This engraving provides the least DMG boost out of all 4.
  • Very beginner-friendly as it affects no active gameplay
  • Malus can be avoided with proper dodging
  • Recommended for newer and ease-of-use players

Propulsion

+3/8/16% Damage

After using Spacebar

  • This engraving provides the third best DMG boost out of all 4.
  • It becomes viable due to Relentless Assault double spacebar and its own cooldown-reduction mechanic.
  • “Assault” lasts 6s, while Propulsion only lasts 5s
  • Recommended for experienced players.

Mass Increase

+4/10/18% Attack Power

-10% Attack Speed

  • This engraving provides the second best DMG boost out of all 4.
  • Attack speed malus is partially mitigated by the “Assault” 8% ATK buff and Attack Speed Tripods
  • Pistoleer only gets 120% ATK Speed through “Assault” and Yearning
  • Recommended for experienced players.

Raid Captain

+4/8.8/18% Damage

at max Move Speed (140%)

Scales with Move Speed

  • This engraving provides the best DMG boost out of all 4.
  • It becomes viable with the “Quick Pace” and Yearning/ “Assault” MV buff.
  • Has to be cast before every set of skills to gain the RC DMG buff
  • Strictest and most limiting requirement as Quick Pace only lasts 4s.
  • Skill rotation will desync after a while, making maintaining alot more complex
  • Recommended for min-maxers.

FAQ: Pistoleer

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord #deadeye
This section is ever-growing, and new FAQ submissions are always welcome.

What is “Relentless Assault”?
Relentless Assault replaces Deadeye’s innate movement ability, aka its spacebar, with its own version.
Deadeye’s spacebar is replaced with a shorter, faster animation and has several unique properties.
Relentless Assault has two stacks, which means that two independent spacebars can be performed with their own cooldown.
After using the spacebar, you will gain the “[Assault]” buff for 5s, which grants 8% Attack/Movement speed bonus and 5% Cooldown Reduction.
Additionally, using a pistol skill, which connects to an enemy, will reduce your current spacebar ability by 0.1s
This means that in effect your spacebar has an approximate 5-6s cooldown.

Critical Rate Sources

Crit Stat

0.03579% Crit Rate per 1 point of Crit (100 Crit ~ 3,57%)

Bracelet

Relic = 41 to 100 Crit =  1.47% to 3.58%

Ancient = 61 to 120 Crit =  2.18% to 4.30%

(Additional effects can also provide brief Crit buffs.)

Gear Set

Preordained Diligence: 15% at 5 stacks.

Shrieking Hallucination: 20%/25%/28%

Adrenaline

Level 1/2/3: 5%/10%/15% at 6 stacks.

Precise Dagger

Level 3: 20%

Spec/Crit or Spec/Swift necklace?

Spec/Crit is the standard stat recommendation for the necklace.

Spec/Swift is viable, but weaker than Spec/Crit under most circumstances

Spec/Swift only outbeats Crit/Spec under several scenarios:
1) Additional crit synergy in your party (GS. Arcana, etc)
(Crit/Spec overcrits over 100% and doesn't gain the same benefit)
2) Additional crit rate sources from bracelets (Precise, Expose Weakness, etc.)

Conviction/Judgment?

Recommended for use. Using Desperado/Equilibrium will trigger Conviction/Judgment effect nearly guaranteed.
Under the Judgment effect, battle resource recovery is doubled and every ability casted gets additional cooldown reduction.

The battle resource recovery is especially important as Pistoleer, particularly with added swiftness, can run out of mana.
